Actress Ini Edo has called on all women to participate actively in the Ekiti governorship candidate. In a video shared on her Instagram page, Edo insisted the active participation of women in politics will go a long way to bring about the desired change in the state.   Portable calls out Burna Boy over alleged intellectual theft     Tems diagnosed with ‘reflux laryngitis’,…     Malabu Oil Block: I’ve been vindicated, says Adoke   The 40-year-old Akwa-Ibom indigene, reminded Ekiti women that their vote represents their voices, as such, it should be deployed maximally on the said day of the election. Captioning the video, the movie star wrote: “Ekiti women, voting is not only your right but your POWER! Your power to get better hospitals, good schools for your children, and good roads. “Go out in mass to your polling unit on the 18th of June 2022 and let your leaders hear you as you vote for your preferred candidate. You can make a change if you vote. #EkitiDecides2022.”